In addition to the terms of the AGPL-3.0, the following additional restrictions
apply to this software and all derivative works:

1. SANCTIONS COMPLIANCE REQUIREMENT

   Any derivative work, modification, or redistribution of this software MUST
   retain and not disable, remove, circumvent, or weaken the Private Proof of
   Innocence (PPOI) integration or any other sanctions compliance mechanisms
   present in this software.

   All PPOI verification MUST use the official PPOI aggregator node provided
   at https://ppoi.fdi.network/ (or any successor URL designated by the PPOI
   network operators). You may NOT substitute, replace, or redirect PPOI
   verification to any other endpoint, self-hosted node, or mock service.

   Specifically, you may NOT:
   - Remove or disable PPOI verification
   - Modify the software to bypass sanctions screening
   - Create derivative works that allow sanctioned funds to receive privacy
   - Weaken, circumvent, or defeat any compliance mechanisms
   - Replace or redirect the PPOI aggregator endpoint away from the official
     PPOI network at https://ppoi.fdi.network/

   Any derivative work that removes or weakens PPOI or sanctions compliance
   is NOT authorized under this license and constitutes a breach of this
   license.

2. NON-COMMERCIAL DISTRIBUTION

   The software itself may not be sold or commercially distributed.

   You MAY:
   - Use the software for any personal purpose, including profitable activities
   - Study and reference the source code
   - Create derivative works (subject to term 1 above)

   You MAY NOT:
   - Sell copies of this software or derivative works
   - Charge fees to access or download this software
   - Include this software in a commercial product offered for sale
   - Offer hosting or access to this software as a paid service

3. NO ENDORSEMENT

